<emphasis id="B921EB625567FF8B528DBD8FFE8DF93B" bold="true" box="[189,311,1686,1712]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA37705567FF8B528DBDDCFCAFF8C2" blockId="13.[188,1401,1733,1865]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Body (
<figureCitation id="136E2BF55567FF8B5322BDDCFE2FF954" box="[274,405,1733,1759]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[292,1296,745,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-129@6.[285,1303,741,1820]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 1. Species of the genera Apatopsis Semenov, 1891, Habrochiton Semenov Tjan-Shansky, 1907 and Habrobates Semenov, 1903, habitus. A. A. grombczewskii Semenov, 1891, ♀, paralectotype (ZIN), dorsal view. B. Ditto, ventral view. C. Habrochiton vernus Semenov-Tjan-Shansky, 1907, ♀, paralectotype (ZIN), dorsal view. D. Ditto, ventral view. E. Habrobates vernalis Semenov, 1903, ♂, paralectotype (ZIN), dorsal view. F. Ditto, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419427/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 1C–D</figureCitation>
) brown, slender, elongate-oval, completely covered with moderately dense short (
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF35567FF8B52F7BDF0FE86F889" authorityName="Semenov Tjan-Shansky" authorityYear="1907" box="[199,316,1769,1794]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Habrochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernus">
<emphasis id="B921EB625567FF8B52F7BDF0FE86F889" box="[199,316,1769,1794]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. vernus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or long (
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF35567FF8B5388BDF0FDD7F889" authorityName="Semenov Tjan-Shansky" authorityYear="1907" box="[440,621,1769,1794]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Habrochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="primaeveris">
<emphasis id="B921EB625567FF8B5388BDF0FDD7F889" box="[440,621,1769,1794]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. primaeveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) longitudinally striated scales, sparse scale-like and simple setae (
<figureCitation id="136E2BF55567FF8B52F8BC12FEA5F8AE" box="[200,287,1803,1829]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,525,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-16@17.[189,1398,525,1888]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 10. Habrochiton vernus Semenov-Tjan-Shansky, 1907, ♀, paralectotype (ZIN),covers and setation. A. Covers of pronotum. B. Ditto, larger scale. C. Elytral covers. a = simple setae; b = scale-like setae; c = scales." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419455/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="4CAD9A955567FF8B53FABC12FD86F8AD" box="[458,572,1803,1830]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="9.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="7.0">7–12 mm</quantity>
. Eyes small circular, moderately convex in dorsal view; surface behind eyes concealed under anterior margin of pronotum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA37705567FF8B528DBC68FACCF825" blockId="13.[189,1398,1904,1966]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Pronotum weakly transverse (1.4 × as wide as long). Anterolateral angles not expressed. Prosternum without transverse triangular depression along anterior margin. Prosternal process short and narrow</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2A67F85564FF88528DBC7DFBE8F862" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419449" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6419449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419449/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" startId="14.[189,232,1892,1918]" targetBox="[189,1398,395,1834]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph id="8BEA37705564FF88528DBC7DFBE8F862" blockId="14.[189,1399,1892,2025]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B921EB625564FF88528DBC7DFEBDF8F4" bold="true" box="[189,263,1892,1919]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF35564FF88533BBC7CFD8EF8F4" authority="Semenov, 1891" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1891" box="[267,564,1893,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Apatopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EB625564FF88533BBC7CFE3AF8F4" box="[267,384,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Apatopsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44A815564FF8853B3BC7CFD8EF8F4" author="Semenov A. P." box="[387,564,1893,1919]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="262 - 382" refId="ref33160" refString="Semenov A. P. 1891. Diagnoses coleopterorum novorum ex Asia centrali et orientali. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae 25: 262 - 382." type="journal article" year="1891">Semenov, 1891</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF35564FF885050BC7CFC1CF8F4" authority="Semenov, 1903" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1903" box="[608,934,1893,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Habrobates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EB625564FF885050BC7CFD51F8F4" box="[608,747,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Habrobates</emphasis>
Semenov, 1903
</taxonomicName>
,details of structure. 
<emphasis id="B921EB625564FF8856B7BC7DFB26F8F5" bold="true" box="[1159,1180,1892,1918]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF35564FF88569BBC7CFECDF829" authority="Semenov, 1891" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Apatopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grombczewskii">
<emphasis id="B921EB625564FF88569BBC7CFACCF8F4" box="[1195,1398,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">A.grombczewskii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44A815564FF88528DBC91FECDF829" author="Semenov A. P." box="[189,375,1928,1954]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="262 - 382" refId="ref33160" refString="Semenov A. P. 1891. Diagnoses coleopterorum novorum ex Asia centrali et orientali. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae 25: 262 - 382." type="journal article" year="1891">Semenov, 1891</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, ♂ (ZIN), pronotum. 
<emphasis id="B921EB625564FF8850B1BC91FD2FF829" bold="true" box="[641,661,1928,1954]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B</emphasis>
. Ditto, scales and seta on pronotum. 
<emphasis id="B921EB625564FF88566EBC91FBC9F829" bold="true" box="[1118,1139,1928,1954]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">C</emphasis>
. Ditto, elytral scales, setation and granulation. 
<emphasis id="B921EB625564FF8853D6BCB2FE41F84E" bold="true" box="[486,507,1963,1989]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D</emphasis>
. Ditto, granule, seta and scales on elytra. 
<emphasis id="B921EB625564FF8851D7BCB2FC41F84E" bold="true" box="[999,1019,1963,1989]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF35564FF88563ABCB5FAF7F84E" authority="Semenov, 1903" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1903" box="[1034,1357,1963,1989]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Habrobates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernalis">
<emphasis id="B921EB625564FF88563ABCB5FB34F84E" box="[1034,1166,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">H. vernalis</emphasis>
Semenov, 1903
</taxonomicName>
, ♂, paralectotype (ZIN), pronotum. 
<emphasis id="B921EB625564FF885006BCD7FDF2F863" bold="true" box="[566,584,1998,2024]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">F</emphasis>
. Scales and spinulose setation on pronotum.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF2A67F85565FF89528DBC7DFAA4F863" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419453" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6419453" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419453/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" startId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" targetBox="[189,1398,457,1853]" targetPageId="15">
<paragraph id="8BEA37705565FF89528DBC7DFAA4F863" blockId="15.[188,1399,1892,2025]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="B921EB625565FF89528DBC7DFEB1F8F4" bold="true" box="[189,267,1892,1919]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 9.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF35565FF895321BC7CFDEDF8F4" authority="Semenov, 1903" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1903" box="[273,599,1893,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Habrobates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EB625565FF895321BC7CFE26F8F4" box="[273,412,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Habrobates</emphasis>
Semenov, 1903
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF35565FF8950BEBC7CFC67F80B" authority="Kuhnelt, 1957" authorityName="Kuhnelt" authorityYear="1957" box="[654,989,1893,1920]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Dietomorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EB625565FF8950BEBC7CFC96F8F4" box="[654,812,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Dietomorpha</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44A815565FF895104BC7CFC67F80B" author="Kuhnelt W." box="[820,989,1893,1920]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="65 - 102" refId="ref31209" refString="Kuhnelt W. 1957. Ergebnisse der Osterreichischen Iran-Expedition 1949 / 50. Die Tenebrioniden Irans. Sitzungsberichte der Osterreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Mathematisch- Naturwissenschaftliche Klasse 166 (2): 65 - 102." type="journal article" year="1957">Kühnelt, 1957</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, details of structure. 
<emphasis id="B921EB625565FF8956FFBC7DFB5EF8F5" bold="true" box="[1231,1252,1892,1918]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">A</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF35565FF8956C3BC7FFEC1F829" authority="Semenov, 1903" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Habrobates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernalis">
<emphasis id="B921EB625565FF8956C3BC7FFACCF8F4" box="[1267,1398,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">H. vernalis</emphasis>
Semenov, 1903
</taxonomicName>
, ♂, paralectotype (ZIN), left elytron. 
<emphasis id="B921EB625565FF895152BC91FCCCF829" bold="true" box="[866,886,1928,1954]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">B</emphasis>
. Ditto, elytral scales and rows of setae. 
<emphasis id="B921EB625565FF89528DBCB2FF68F84E" bold="true" box="[189,210,1963,1989]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">C</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF35565FF8952D4BCB5FD9EF84D" authority="Kuhnelt, 1957" authorityName="Kuhnelt" authorityYear="1957" box="[228,548,1963,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Dietomorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pardalis">
<emphasis id="B921EB625565FF8952D4BCB5FED7F84E" box="[228,365,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. pardalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44A815565FF895347BCB2FD9EF84D" author="Kuhnelt W." box="[375,548,1963,1990]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="65 - 102" refId="ref31209" refString="Kuhnelt W. 1957. Ergebnisse der Osterreichischen Iran-Expedition 1949 / 50. Die Tenebrioniden Irans. Sitzungsberichte der Osterreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Mathematisch- Naturwissenschaftliche Klasse 166 (2): 65 - 102." type="journal article" year="1957">Kühnelt, 1957</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, ♂ (ZIN), pronotum. 
<emphasis id="B921EB625565FF89511EBCB2FCF9F84E" bold="true" box="[814,835,1963,1989]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D</emphasis>
. Ditto, scales, setae and granules in middle of pronotum. 
<emphasis id="B921EB625565FF89530EBCD7FEE8F863" bold="true" box="[318,338,1998,2024]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E</emphasis>
. Ditto, base of left elytron. 
<emphasis id="B921EB625565FF8950A6BCD7FD12F863" bold="true" box="[662,680,1998,2024]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">F</emphasis>
. Ditto, scales, spine-like tubercle and seta on elytron.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BEA3770557AFF96528DBA10FD22FECC" blockId="16.[189,1398,265,327]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">(length 1.7 × width), not raised above procoxae, not protruding. Prosternum very short, near 2 × as long as longitudinal diameter of one procoxa.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA3770557AFF96528DBA77FD91FE7A" blockId="16.[189,1398,366,497]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Elytra elongate-oval (
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF3557AFF96538EBA77FD88FE0C" authorityName="Semenov Tjan-Shansky" authorityYear="1907" box="[446,562,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Habrochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernus">
<emphasis id="B921EB62557AFF96538EBA77FD88FE0C" box="[446,562,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">H. vernus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or triangular, almost wedge-shaped (
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF3557AFF9651C4BA77FB1DFE0C" authorityName="Semenov Tjan-Shansky" authorityYear="1907" box="[1012,1191,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Habrochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="primaeveris">
<emphasis id="B921EB62557AFF9651C4BA77FB1DFE0C" box="[1012,1191,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">H. primaeveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Scutellar shield completely (
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF3557AFF965360BA8BFE79FE20" authorityName="Semenov Tjan-Shansky" authorityYear="1907" box="[336,451,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Habrochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernus">
<emphasis id="B921EB62557AFF965360BA8BFE79FE20" box="[336,451,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">H. vernus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or partially concealed (
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF3557AFF9650D2BA8BFC2EFE20" authorityName="Semenov Tjan-Shansky" authorityYear="1907" box="[738,916,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Habrochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="primaeveris">
<emphasis id="B921EB62557AFF9650D2BA8BFC2EFE20" box="[738,916,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">H. primaeveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by elytral base; surface around scutellar shield without triangular depression. Transverse length of one metacoxa less than intercoxal process of abdominal ventrite 1 (
<figureCitation id="136E2BF5557AFF9653F0BACEFDA7FE7A" box="[448,541,471,497]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[292,1296,745,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-129@6.[285,1303,741,1820]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 1. Species of the genera Apatopsis Semenov, 1891, Habrochiton Semenov Tjan-Shansky, 1907 and Habrobates Semenov, 1903, habitus. A. A. grombczewskii Semenov, 1891, ♀, paralectotype (ZIN), dorsal view. B. Ditto, ventral view. C. Habrochiton vernus Semenov-Tjan-Shansky, 1907, ♀, paralectotype (ZIN), dorsal view. D. Ditto, ventral view. E. Habrobates vernalis Semenov, 1903, ♂, paralectotype (ZIN), dorsal view. F. Ditto, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419427/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA3770557AFF96528DB900FD65FC3D" blockId="16.[189,1401,537,950]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Trochanters with very short dense setae. Meso- and metafemora curved outward along elytral lateral vertical side. Pro- and metatibiae weakly curved outward, protibiae (
<figureCitation id="136E2BF5557AFF9651DDB925FBE5FDDD" box="[1005,1119,572,598]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="52.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[290,1286,773,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-71@52.[281,1307,763,1783]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Fig. 26. Protibiae of Pimeliini, optic microscopy. A. Habrochiton vernus Semenov-Tjan-Shansky, 1907, ♂, lectotype (ZIN). B. Habrobates gabrieli (Schuster, 1935) comb. nov., paralectotype (NMB). C. Dietomorpha pardalis Kühnelt, 1957, ♂ (ZIN). D. Mantichorula semenowi Reitter, 1889, ♂ (ZIN). E. Przewalskia dilatata (Reitter, 1887), ♂ (ZIN). F. Apatopsis grombczewskii Semenov, 1891, ♀, paralectotype (ZIN). G. Earophanta serrata (Semenov, 1893), ♂ (ZIN). H. Platyope leucogramma (Pallas, 1773), ♂ (ZIN). Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419501" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419501/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs 26A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136E2BF5557AFF96565CB925FB27FDDD" box="[1132,1181,572,598]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="53.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,449,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-26@53.[189,1398,449,1818]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Fig. 27. Protibiae of Pimeliini, SEM. A. Apatopsis grombczewskii Semenov, 1891, ♀ (ZIN), dorsal view. B. Ditto, apical part. C. Habrobates vernalis Semenov, 1903, ♂, paralectotype (ZIN), ventral view. D. Ditto, dorsal view. E. Habrochiton vernus Semenov-Tjan-Shansky, 1907, dorsal view (ZIN). F. Mantichorula semenowi Reitter, 1889, ♂ (ZIN), ventral view. G. Ditto, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419505/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">27E</figureCitation>
) widened at apex, outer margin of protibia projecting into short rounded process at apex with one (
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF3557AFF9656A4B979FAF0FDF2" authorityName="Semenov Tjan-Shansky" authorityYear="1907" box="[1172,1354,608,633]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Habrochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="primaeveris">
<emphasis id="B921EB62557AFF9656A4B979FAF0FDF2" box="[1172,1354,608,633]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">H. primaeveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or several acutely angulate and closely located (
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF3557AFF9650D2B99AFCE2FD17" authorityName="Semenov Tjan-Shansky" authorityYear="1907" box="[738,856,643,668]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Habrochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernus">
<emphasis id="B921EB62557AFF9650D2B99AFCE2FD17" box="[738,856,643,668]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">H. vernus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) short spines; outer margin armed with very short tubercles with long and thin spines and additionally with long and sparse setaesetae (
<figureCitation id="136E2BF5557AFF9656CDB9BCFAD0FD4B" box="[1277,1386,677,704]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="53.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,449,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-26@53.[189,1398,449,1818]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Fig. 27. Protibiae of Pimeliini, SEM. A. Apatopsis grombczewskii Semenov, 1891, ♀ (ZIN), dorsal view. B. Ditto, apical part. C. Habrobates vernalis Semenov, 1903, ♂, paralectotype (ZIN), ventral view. D. Ditto, dorsal view. E. Habrochiton vernus Semenov-Tjan-Shansky, 1907, dorsal view (ZIN). F. Mantichorula semenowi Reitter, 1889, ♂ (ZIN), ventral view. G. Ditto, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419505/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 27E</figureCitation>
). Protibial terminal spurs strongly elongated, extending to base of protarsomere 5, mesotibial terminal spurs extending to base of mesotarsomere 3, metatibial terminal spurs extending to midlength of metatarsomere 1. Outer and inner protibial terminal spurs subequal in length, inner meso- and metatibial terminal spurs longer than outer one; spurs flattened, outer spur moderately narrowed to apex, acutely angulate at apex. Protarsi laterally not flattened, covered with short strong setae. Meso- and metatarsi flattened from sides, covered with long fine setae dorsally and shorter and stronger setae ventrally. Tarsal claws elongated, thin, weakly curved outward.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA3770557AFF9652DAB8C4FE25FC7C" blockId="16.[189,727,989,1051]" box="[234,415,989,1015]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B921EB62557AFF9652DAB8C4FE25FC7C" bold="true" box="[234,415,989,1015]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Male genitalia</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA3770557AFF96528DBF19FD6DFB90" blockId="16.[189,727,989,1051]" box="[189,727,1024,1051]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Male genitalia identical to those in 
<taxonomicName id="4C554CF3557AFF96506BBF18FD6AFB90" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1891" box="[603,720,1025,1051]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Apatopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EB62557AFF96506BBF18FD6AFB90" box="[603,720,1025,1051]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Apatopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA3770557AFF9652DABF5BFACDFBF4" blockId="16.[188,1400,1090,1257]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B921EB62557AFF9652DABF5BFECBFBD7" bold="true" box="[234,369,1090,1116]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Ovipositor</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="136E2BF5557AFF9653B1BF5BFDB9FBD6" box="[385,515,1090,1117]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="36.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,638,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-86@36.[200,1386,634,1818]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="Fig. 15. Habrochiton vernus Semenov-Tjan-Shansky, 1907 (ZIN), genitalia. A. Tegmen of aedeagus, ventrally. B. Ditto, dorsally. C. Ditto, laterally. D. Median lobe, ventrally. E. Ditto, dorsally. F. Ditto, laterally. G. Spiculum gastrale. H. ♂, inner sternite VIII. I. ♀, inner sternite VIII and spiculum ventrale. J. Ovipositor, ventrally. K. Ditto, dorsally. L. Ditto, laterally. Not to scale. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419471" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419471/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 15J–L</figureCitation>
) Very short, paraproct slightly longer than coxite. Paraproct with thin baculi, indistinct at apical third.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA3770557AFF96528FBF91FABCFB62" blockId="16.[188,1400,1090,1257]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Coxite lobe baculi short, more sclerotized in apical part, with additional sclerotized projection on ventral side; lobe II very narrow (
<figureCitation id="136E2BF5557AFF9653D7BFB2FDEAFB4D" box="[487,592,1195,1222]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="36.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,638,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-86@36.[200,1386,634,1818]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="Fig. 15. Habrochiton vernus Semenov-Tjan-Shansky, 1907 (ZIN), genitalia. A. Tegmen of aedeagus, ventrally. B. Ditto, dorsally. C. Ditto, laterally. D. Median lobe, ventrally. E. Ditto, dorsally. F. Ditto, laterally. G. Spiculum gastrale. H. ♂, inner sternite VIII. I. ♀, inner sternite VIII and spiculum ventrale. J. Ovipositor, ventrally. K. Ditto, dorsally. L. Ditto, laterally. Not to scale. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419471" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419471/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 15L</figureCitation>
); lobe III slightly longer, conical, without additional projecting apical processes; lobe IV membranous, conical, rounded at apex, densely pubescent with long setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA3770557AFF9652DABE09FDA4FAC6" blockId="16.[189,542,1296,1357]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B921EB62557AFF9652DABE09FE54FAA1" bold="true" box="[234,494,1296,1322]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Female genital ducts</emphasis>
Destroyed during preparation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
